content.webTitle: Pick of the week: London: Clubs

fields.headline: Pick of the Week: Clubs
fields.bodyText: Spent Lock Tavern, NW1, Sunday 26 Apr A lazy Sunday afternoon and evening. in the company of DFA's Moon Unit, who plays live, plus Frankmusik and Nick Cave –but not that Nick Cave – on the decks. And it's free to get in. Shoreditch Is Shit 333, EC1, Tuesday 28 Apr Shoreditch Is Shit and Plain Janes combine for a massive foam party with Yo! Mama upstairs bringing Bmore club and baile funk to Mother Bar. Action Aid Presents 6º Live ICA, SW1, Wednesday 29 Apr It's rare that you get to campaign for women's rights in the developing world and party to thecocknbullkid and Micachu, but tonight is that night. Annie Mac Presents KOKO, NW1, Thursday 30 Apr The superstar DJ brings her mates to London, and what a list of mates it is: Little Boots, the Count & Sinden, Toddla T and Plan B all make an appearance. Forever Heavenly Corsica Studios, SE17, Friday 1 May One of the bank holiday weekend's most impressive lineups, with Playgroup's Trevor Jackson at the helm with Bassclef, Bullion, Raf Daddy and Joe from Hot Chip.
